main event: Sgt. Francis Young reported observing six unidentified flying objects at 0200 EST on 20 July 1952.
interesting points: The objects were reported to be bright and maneuvering for approximately twelve minutes., Some objects were in formation while others were scattered., The objects were flying at a very high altitude., The observation was verified by another unidentified airman., The report was part of an Air Intelligence Information Report from Project Blue Book.
witness description: Sgt. Francis Young and an unidentified airman
